## Current Focus
hypothesis: Trailing commas after JSX props in CoverLetterPage component call are causing Babel parser error
test: Remove trailing commas from JSX props and verify compilation succeeds
expecting: Vite dev server/build should compile without errors
next_action: Request human verification that the app runs correctly

## Symptoms
expected: The app should compile and run without errors
actual: Vite dev server or build fails with the shown Babel syntax error
errors: [plugin:vite:react-babel] E:\VS-projects\job-app-assistant\client\src\pages\ReviewFinalizePage.tsx: Unexpected token (2227:77)
reproduction: Running `npm run dev` or `npm run build` triggers the error
timeline: Started right after the cover letter extraction refactoring commit (071b03f)

## Eliminated

## Evidence
- timestamp: 2026-03-29T00:00:00.000Z
  checked: Lines 2220-2280 of ReviewFinalizePage.tsx
  found: Trailing commas exist after JSX props in CoverLetterPage component call at lines 2227, 2235, 2239, 2242, 2256, 2265, 2272
  implication: These commas are invalid JSX syntax and cause Babel parser to fail
- timestamp: 2026-03-29T00:00:00.000Z
  checked: Vite dev server startup
  found: Vite dev server started successfully on localhost:5174 without any Babel errors
  implication: Fix successfully resolved the parsing error
- timestamp: 2026-03-29T00:00:00.000Z
  checked: TypeScript compilation
  found: npx tsc --noEmit --skipLibCheck passed without errors
  implication: No TypeScript issues introduced by the fix

## Resolution
root_cause: Trailing commas after JSX props in CoverLetterPage component call (lines 2227, 2235, 2239, 2242, 2256, 2265, 2272). In JSX, props should not be separated by commas - they should only be separated by whitespace/newlines.
fix: Removed 7 trailing commas from JSX props in the CoverLetterPage component call
verification: Vite dev server starts successfully without Babel errors; TypeScript compilation passes without errors
files_changed: ["src/pages/ReviewFinalizePage.tsx"]
